The Kroc Institute’s mission is to advance knowledge and understanding of the causes of violent conflict and the conditions for peace.

The Kroc Institute’s vision is a world in which people live together in peace.
What is the Kroc Institute’s approach to research?
The Kroc Institute takes a multidisciplinary approach to research, drawing on the expertise of scholars from a variety of disciplines, including anthropology, history, political science, sociology, and theology. We also work closely with practitioners in the field to ensure that our research is relevant and practical.

- The causes of violent conflict

The Kroc Institute uses a variety of research methods, including field research, surveys, interviews, and focus groups. We also use a variety of data sources, including primary and secondary sources, as well as qualitative and quantitative data.

The Kroc Institute’s research outputs include books, articles, policy briefs, and working papers. We also produce a variety of other publications, including newsletters, blogs, and podcasts.

The Kroc Institute’s impact can be seen in the form of the knowledge and understanding that we have gained about the causes of violent conflict and the conditions for peace. This knowledge has been used to inform the work of practitioners in the field, as well as to shape public policy.
